    "abstractNote": "An examination of the citation by St. Paul (<i>Epist. to Titus</i> 12) of a famous hexameter attributed to Epimenides, while tracing its polemical use by Pagans  and  Christians  and discussing modern interpretations, highlights the sarcastic employment of the verse (against Paul) by the emperor Julian in his work <i>Contra Galilaeos</i> and the reaction of the Antiochean exegetes Theodore of Mopsuestia and John Chrysostom.",
